cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving place recognition for mobile autonomy using radar sensors. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper discusses integrating a rotationally-invariant metric embedding for radar scans into a sequence-based trajectory matching system typically used for visual sensors. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper mentions using a learned rotational invariance approach. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that could potentially apply to this paper as it involves developing an application for autonomous vehicles. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve natural language processing techniques for processing the radar data.
